# Adobo Sauce

## Ingredients

- 1/2 cup greek yogurt (nonfat or any type)
- 1/2 cup cottage cheese
- 1 garlic clove
- 2 tbsp lime juice
- 1 tsp smoked paprika
- 1/4 tsp chili powder
- Shake of cayenne pepper
- Shake of cumin
- Pinch of salt
- Pinch of pepper
- Water (if needed for texture)

## Instructions

1. Add everything into a blender,
making sure the yogurt and cottage
cheese go in first so it blends easier.
2. Blend until completely smooth.
3. Taste and adjust. If the sauce is
too thick, add a small splash of
water or more lime juice and
blend again until it reaches your
preferred consistency.